race.comment: OUI OUI OUI (3) classy mare starting to put it all together. Made it two straight victories from the wide gate when a comfortable winner over 1200m at this track. Has further upside and expected to cope with the rise in weight from the good draw. KYEEMA (10) tough gelding who looks to have come back in good order after his sound second over 1250m at Randwick Kensington. Gets the right run and expected to figure prominently. APACHE BREEZE (8) underrated gelding who meets OUI OUI OUI much better at the weights today with the claim. Looking for the 1400m now and expect to see him a little closer to the speed. Value chance. MISS SPACEGIRL (6) talented mare near her top third-up. Has the speed to get across from the sticky gate with the claim and not without top-three claims. DANISH PRINCE (9) will roll forward again and give a ton of cheek with Roper's 2kg claim. No shock to see him win again.
